00:59:33,160 --> 00:59:35,162
because so many doors
were being closed,

957
00:59:35,194 --> 00:59:36,664
but I had to keep going.

958
00:59:37,798 --> 00:59:44,104
You know when you have this
deep... like deep inside you:

959
00:59:44,136 --> 00:59:45,472
"He's coming back."

960
00:59:45,504 --> 00:59:47,540
And sometimes
the other mind told you,

961
00:59:47,573 --> 00:59:52,378
"Wake up, this is
a cold case in Pakistan,

962
00:59:52,412 --> 00:59:53,781
it's not going to happen."

963
00:59:53,814 --> 00:59:55,415
and you're like
going back and forth

964
00:59:55,448 --> 00:59:57,251
with your head
like a crazy man,

965
00:59:57,283 --> 01:00:00,319
it's the same thing. And
on the other side you're like,

966
01:00:00,352 --> 01:00:02,488
all these
people sending letters,

967
01:00:02,522 --> 01:00:05,826
people calling, there
is a hope that somebody will

968
01:00:05,859 --> 01:00:08,662
do something so that's
the only thing that's making me

969
01:00:08,694 --> 01:00:11,664
have a huge
hope he's coming back.

970
01:00:11,698 --> 01:00:14,368
On the other hand
I look at the case...

971
01:00:14,401 --> 01:00:16,504
Until the guy
got arrested.

972
01:00:20,539 --> 01:00:22,842
<i>Roughly six months
after I was in jail</i>

973
01:00:22,876 --> 01:00:26,814
<i>a DEA agent comes
and he shows me two photos</i>

974
01:00:26,847 --> 01:00:29,450
<i>and asked me do I recognize
anyone in these photos.</i>

975
01:00:29,482 --> 01:00:31,350
<i>I immediately picked out Rai.
I was like: "That's Rai."</i>

976
01:00:31,383 --> 01:00:33,453
And he goes, "Well his
name is Razmik Minasian."

977
01:00:33,486 --> 01:00:34,854
And this is where I would
find out that he

978
01:00:34,888 --> 01:00:37,758
had been using
an alias the whole time.

979
01:00:37,790 --> 01:00:39,660
And I'm like: "Cool,
well how did you guys get him?"

980
01:00:39,693 --> 01:00:42,863
What had happened was a Swedish
woman was traveling in

981
01:00:42,896 --> 01:00:45,365
<i>from JFK airport, doing
