982
01:00:45,397 --> 01:00:47,501
<i>but she lost
her luggage at JFK.</i>

983
01:00:47,533 --> 01:00:49,769
So she continued on
her itinerary to LAX.

984
01:00:49,803 --> 01:00:51,839
<i>They found the drugs
in the wall of her suitcase,</i>

985
01:00:51,872 --> 01:00:53,740
<i>built professionally
into the suitcase,</i>

986
01:00:53,772 --> 01:00:55,508
<i>and they arrested both her</i>

987
01:00:55,542 --> 01:00:57,411
and the man that I
had known as Rai Ghazarian.

988
01:00:57,443 --> 01:01:00,080
Except he posted bail
under the name Razmik Minasian.

989
01:01:01,414 --> 01:01:03,249
<i>My mom's private investigator
hears about this,</i>

990
01:01:03,283 --> 01:01:05,252
<i>brings it to the
attention of the DEA</i>

991
01:01:05,285 --> 01:01:08,455
<i>and hey this sounds a lot
like that guy who set up Erik.</i>

992
01:01:08,488 --> 01:01:10,857
<i>So they rearrest him,
deny him bail...</i>

993
01:01:10,890 --> 01:01:13,193
<i>They let the Swedish girl
go back to her country</i>

994
01:01:13,225 --> 01:01:15,194
without being charged
in less than two weeks

995
01:01:15,227 --> 01:01:18,564
simply because her story
matched mine and several others.

996
01:01:18,597 --> 01:01:20,500
So when I heard about this
I felt great.

997
01:01:20,533 --> 01:01:22,468
I'm like: "Great, someone's
not in jail because of me."

998
01:01:22,502 --> 01:01:24,538
That's awesome.
I felt good about that.

999
01:01:24,571 --> 01:01:27,708
So now here I got the
DEA guy telling me this story

1000
01:01:27,740 --> 01:01:29,809
and I'm asking
what happens now?

1001
01:01:29,843 --> 01:01:31,678
"What are you guys doing
to get me out of here?"

1002
01:01:31,711 --> 01:01:36,383
And I could tell by his
expression that he felt bad.

1003
01:01:37,651 --> 01:01:39,853
And I'm like:
"What's going on?"

1004
01:01:39,885 --> 01:01:41,420
He goes: "I've never
seen this before."

1005
01:01:41,453 --> 01:01:43,390
I go: "What do you mean?"

1006
01:01:43,423 --> 01:01:45,158
He said: "I've never actually
met someone who's innocent."

1007
01:01:45,892 --> 01:01:49,230
They let her go home
and arrested him.

1008
01:01:51,932 --> 01:01:56,303
But nobody would do anything
to help me get Erik home.

1009
01:01:59,673 --> 01:02:01,808
He goes: "If this
had been done in America

1010
01:02:01,841 --> 01:02:03,544
you'd be
going home tonight.

1011
01:02:03,577 --> 01:02:05,379
Because since it's
done here in Pakistan,

1012
01:02:05,412 --> 01:02:07,747
you still have to go through
the legal system here.

1013
01:02:07,781 --> 01:02:10,350
It sucked being in jail
for something I didn't do

1014
01:02:10,383 --> 01:02:12,785
and no one believing me,
but believe it or not

1015
01:02:12,818 --> 01:02:15,555
it sucks a lot worse when
people actually believe you,

1016
01:02:15,589 --> 01:02:17,691
and the people
you assumed could...

1017
01:02:17,723 --> 01:02:19,626
And the people that you know
that could do something

1018
01:02:19,658 --> 01:02:22,396
about it believe you, but choose
not to do anything about it.

1019
01:02:24,531 --> 01:02:26,266
Yeah, no that's great.

1020
01:02:26,298 --> 01:02:27,867
OK, so I need to
ask you, so what was the

1021
01:02:27,901 --> 01:02:29,403
involvement
with your friend

1022
01:02:29,435 --> 01:02:31,704
that was the PI?
Can we call him and see?

1023
01:02:31,738 --> 01:02:33,807
Yeah, let's just see.

1024
01:02:33,839 --> 01:02:35,608
so and
then my question is...

1025
01:02:35,642 --> 01:02:37,743
So I really
want to interview Rai

1026
01:02:37,776 --> 01:02:40,313
but I'm having a really
hard time tracking him down.

1027
01:02:40,347 --> 01:02:42,682
I have a phone number
that's disconnected.

1028
01:02:42,716 --> 01:02:46,520
I found an address on the
Internet that could be his...

1029
01:02:46,553 --> 01:02:50,257
I found a bunch of
businesses that he used to have

1030
01:02:50,289 --> 01:02:51,958
that seemed
to all dissolve

1031
01:02:51,992 --> 01:02:53,859
and all those numbers
are disconnected.

1032
01:02:53,892 --> 01:02:56,262
I sent him a message,
I found him on Facebook

1033
01:02:56,296 --> 01:02:57,631
but we're not connected

1034
01:02:57,664 --> 01:02:59,332
so he hasn't
seen the message yet.

1035
01:02:59,365 --> 01:03:01,267
But we're
kind of at the end

1036
01:03:01,301 --> 01:03:03,403
and I really didn't find...

1037
01:03:03,435 --> 01:03:06,439
How I could go about
finding an address,

1038
01:03:06,472 --> 01:03:07,941
an email, a phone number.

1039
01:03:08,841 --> 01:03:12,678
<i>If you
have either his full name</i>

1040
01:03:12,711 --> 01:03:18,551
<i>and middle initial or
his social security number</i>

1041
01:03:18,584 --> 01:03:22,455
<i>or a former address</i>

1042
01:03:22,488 --> 01:03:26,457
<i>I can find out
where he is now.</i>

1043
01:03:26,459 --> 01:03:27,560
- Okay.
- A former address?

1044
01:03:27,593 --> 01:03:29,296
A former address?

1045
01:03:29,328 --> 01:03:32,466
what if it was an old...
an old business address

1046
01:03:32,499 --> 01:03:34,434
or one that he used
for a business?

1047
01:03:34,466 --> 01:03:35,801
Would that work?

1048
01:03:35,834 --> 01:03:37,603
<i>Yeah,
that would work.</i>

1049
01:03:37,636 --> 01:03:40,274
<i>And it probably would
take about an hour</i>

1050
01:03:40,307 --> 01:03:43,910
<i>to get the
complete background on him.</i>

1051
01:03:44,877 --> 01:03:45,812
Some of
the superintendents

1052
01:03:45,845 --> 01:03:46,747
started liking me,

1053
01:03:46,780 --> 01:03:48,015
one in particular

1054
01:03:48,048 --> 01:03:49,582
was a man named Hijuub.

1055
01:03:49,615 --> 01:03:50,850
He's the one who would
introduce me

1056
01:03:50,883 --> 01:03:52,852
to the
Palestinian hijackers.

1057
01:03:52,885 --> 01:03:55,921
<i>The hijacking
of Pan Am flight 73 is over</i>

1058
01:03:55,955 --> 01:03:57,991
<i>but the cost
has been very high.</i>

1059
01:03:58,024 --> 01:04:00,794
<i>Many passengers who
were on board are in shock.</i>

1060
01:04:00,827 --> 01:04:03,629
<i>many have been wounded
in the final orgy of violence,</i>

1061
01:04:03,662 --> 01:04:06,800
<i>and some passengers
plus two of the hijackers</i>

1062
01:04:06,832 --> 01:04:08,434
<i>have been killed.</i>

1063
01:04:09,669 --> 01:04:11,972
these guys were happy
that their plan had failed

1064
01:04:12,004 --> 01:04:13,839
because their
mission was to kill themselves

1065
01:04:13,872 --> 01:04:15,541
and kill everyone
on board that plane.

1066
01:04:15,575 --> 01:04:18,011
what did happen, was
their actions led to

1067
01:04:18,044 --> 01:04:19,647
23 people being killed.

1068
01:04:20,613 --> 01:04:22,381
The first person
I meet was Fahaad.

1069
01:04:22,414 --> 01:04:23,050
Fahaad was the youngest
and by this time he's

1070
01:04:23,082 --> 01:04:24,885
in his thirties.

1071
01:04:24,917 --> 01:04:27,787
He's a big man and
he's wearing a big muumuu.

1072
01:04:29,089 --> 01:04:30,624
The hijackers are
celebrities in here.

1073
01:04:30,656 --> 01:04:31,691
I'm a celebrity in here.

1074
01:04:32,892 --> 01:04:35,828
The future prime minister
of Pakistan is up in "A class".

1075
01:04:35,861 --> 01:04:38,798
His name is Yousaf Gilani
he's a celebrity in there.

1076
01:04:38,832 --> 01:04:40,400
And then you've got
political officials

1077
01:04:40,432 --> 01:04:42,001
but there's
really only a few of us

1078
01:04:42,035 --> 01:04:43,370
who everyone knows of.

1079
01:04:44,571 --> 01:04:47,641
So I somehow become
friends with these guys.

1080
01:04:47,673 --> 01:04:49,942
They order...
They make food for us,

1081
01:04:49,975 --> 01:04:52,878
we sit around, we drink Pepsi

1082
01:04:52,912 --> 01:04:54,881
and some sweet dish
they just happen to have,

1083
01:04:54,914 --> 01:04:56,649
and their rooms
are really nice actually

1084
01:04:56,682 --> 01:04:58,484
there's
a carpet on the floor.

1085
01:04:58,517 --> 01:05:00,553
They prayed, they ate food,

1086
01:05:00,586 --> 01:05:03,456
and tried to get through
each day as easily as possible.

1087
01:05:04,758 --> 01:05:06,626
When I got moved nine
and a half months later

1088
01:05:06,658 --> 01:05:08,427
from death row to two cell

1089
01:05:08,461 --> 01:05:10,597
I was able to
socialize with these guys more.

1090
01:05:10,629 --> 01:05:12,131
Go have breakfast
and lunch with them

1091
01:05:12,164 --> 01:05:14,800
and swap
books over the wall.

1092
01:05:14,834 --> 01:05:18,071
But one thing that the hijackers
had, which was a big deal,

1093
01:05:18,104 --> 01:05:19,906
was they had
connections with the guard.

1094
01:05:19,939 --> 01:05:21,975
The guards
wouldn't search the room.

1095
01:05:22,008 --> 01:05:24,044
The hijackers were left alone
and they had a lot of clout.

1096
01:05:24,077 --> 01:05:25,713
They had something
that I definitely needed.

1097
01:05:32,685 --> 01:05:38,058
How did you get
a camera inside prison?

1098
01:05:38,091 --> 01:05:40,794
I got a camera into the prison
because of one of the hijackers,

1099
01:05:40,827 --> 01:05:43,562
Fahaad got it in for me.

1100
01:05:43,595 --> 01:05:47,400
I wanted to take some photos
and he got it in.

1101
01:05:47,434 --> 01:05:49,136
Like what
would happen if they found...

1102
01:05:49,169 --> 01:05:51,538
Like people don't have
cameras in prison, do they?

1103
01:05:51,571 --> 01:05:54,473
People aren't supposed to have
a lot of things in prison,

1104
01:05:54,506 --> 01:05:56,075
but we have them.
if you get caught with them

1105
01:05:56,109 --> 01:05:58,812
you get in trouble. Simple.

1106
01:05:58,845 --> 01:06:00,647
Getting in trouble is
getting beat, punished,

1107
01:06:00,680 --> 01:06:01,749
thrown into kasoari.

1108
01:06:02,881 --> 01:06:04,684
Privileges taken away.

1109
01:06:04,716 --> 01:06:06,153
But
how do you get them?

1110
01:06:06,185 --> 01:06:07,988
You actually just
pay people on the outside?

1111
01:06:08,021 --> 01:06:11,124
Yeah! People...
Guards smuggle things in,

1112
01:06:11,156 --> 01:06:13,526
religious teachers
smuggle things in,

1113
01:06:13,560 --> 01:06:15,095
prisoners smuggle things in,

1114
01:06:15,127 --> 01:06:17,696
the canteen smuggles things in.

1115
01:06:17,729 --> 01:06:19,198
Guys throw things
over the wall.

1116
01:06:19,231 --> 01:06:21,434
Hell fuck, if we had
drones back in the day

1117
01:06:21,468 --> 01:06:23,636
you'd see drones dropping things
left and right.

1118
01:06:25,738 --> 01:06:26,839
Wow, that's amazing.

1119
01:06:26,872 --> 01:06:28,675
I'm glad I got some photos.

1120
01:06:28,707 --> 01:06:32,546
I had the camera for I think
two, maybe three days.

1121
01:06:32,578 --> 01:06:33,780
And that's what
I was able to get

1122
01:06:33,812 --> 01:06:35,749
in those two
or three days.

1123
01:06:35,781 --> 01:06:38,117
It started with food. Well
then it got to things bigger.

1124
01:06:38,151 --> 01:06:40,720
"Hey, I'll give you
1,000 rupees for a cell phone."

1125
01:06:40,752 --> 01:06:42,689
Guy brings me
a cell phone.

1126
01:06:42,722 --> 01:06:45,959
I'm able to find a signal
in a corner of my room

1127
01:06:45,992 --> 01:06:47,493
and at night I'm able
to communicate

1128
01:06:47,526 --> 01:06:49,463
with my family
and my friends.

1129
01:06:49,495 --> 01:06:51,497
The first time
I go to talk to Erik...

1130
01:06:51,531 --> 01:06:52,966
First of all I was blown
'cause I was like:

1131
01:06:52,999 --> 01:06:55,234
"How the hell did you
get a cell phone?"

1132
01:06:55,267 --> 01:06:57,102
And then at the same token
I was like: "Of course,

1133
01:06:57,135 --> 01:07:00,172
it's you, it's Erik."
You know. And we talked about

1134
01:07:00,205 --> 01:07:03,609
how he had made friends
with some people in there.

1135
01:07:03,642 --> 01:07:08,048
We talked about how initially
it was super, super, super hard

1136
01:07:08,080 --> 01:07:09,982
kinda being the
American so to speak.

1137
01:07:11,017 --> 01:07:13,153
We talked about how he
learned different languages.

1138
01:07:13,185 --> 01:07:14,988
How he
cultivated relationships.

1139
01:07:15,021 --> 01:07:16,756
How he was able to
get some DVD's and movies

1140
01:07:16,789 --> 01:07:19,526
that I had done
that he had watched.

1141
01:07:21,127 --> 01:07:23,129
And it just
was good, you know,

1142
01:07:23,162 --> 01:07:27,600
And we still just
believed that eventually

1143
01:07:27,633 --> 01:07:28,901
he would come home.

1144
01:07:37,609 --> 01:07:39,546
During this whole time
I'm still learning the language.

1145
01:07:39,578 --> 01:07:40,981
I'm still learning Urdu.

1146
01:07:41,914 --> 01:07:43,249
And I'm also
trying to work on my case.

1147
01:07:43,283 --> 01:07:45,018
I'd finally
gotten a lawyer

1148
01:07:45,051 --> 01:07:47,087
who was just a piece
of shit lawyer to agree to

1149
01:07:47,120 --> 01:07:49,055
take my case
for 2,000 dollars

1150
01:07:49,088 --> 01:07:51,825
which is still five times more
than anyone else would have paid

1151
01:07:51,857 --> 01:07:55,095
but it's a lot less than a lot
of lawyers are asking me for.

1152
01:07:55,127 --> 01:07:58,899
and I would go back and
forth to court so many times

1153
01:07:58,932 --> 01:08:01,134
and nothing would happen. either
the judge wouldn't show up,

1154
01:08:01,167 --> 01:08:02,602
the prosecutor
wouldn't show up,

1155
01:08:02,635 --> 01:08:04,236
my own lawyer
wouldn't show up.

1156
01:08:04,269 --> 01:08:09,175
What we needed for the
courts, was Razmik Menasian

1157
01:08:10,176 --> 01:08:12,913
to sign a statement
stating that

1158
01:08:12,946 --> 01:08:15,281
he'd never told Erik
about the drugs

1159
01:08:15,314 --> 01:08:19,552
and that might,
might you know, do some good.

1160
01:08:21,988 --> 01:08:24,057
I had found out
where he lived

1161
01:08:24,958 --> 01:08:27,727
and I found out
he had two kids

1162
01:08:27,760 --> 01:08:29,829
and I'm not
a vindictive woman,

1163
01:08:29,861 --> 01:08:33,632
but I was
fighting for my son.

1164
01:08:33,665 --> 01:08:35,101
I wrote him a letter

1165
01:08:36,168 --> 01:08:39,705
and I told him
how Erik couldn't believe

1166
01:08:39,739 --> 01:08:42,943
that his friend Rai
would do this to him.

1167
01:08:42,976 --> 01:08:46,313
I mean Rai was his friend,
he was just in shock.

1168
01:08:46,346 --> 01:08:48,815
And I wrote in there
how Erik was being starved,

1169
01:08:48,847 --> 01:08:50,883
and tortured, and beaten.

1170
01:08:50,917 --> 01:08:53,019
You know I said
he can't believe

1171
01:08:53,052 --> 01:08:54,922
you would do this to him.

1172
01:08:56,055 --> 01:09:00,894
And then I went on and I said:
"How maybe if he would confess

1173
01:09:01,927 --> 01:09:04,830
that maybe the courts would look
at that

1174
01:09:04,864 --> 01:09:07,801
and grant Erik clemency."

1175
01:09:10,770 --> 01:09:12,272
And then I went
one step further,

1176
01:09:12,305 --> 01:09:15,107
and I'm ashamed of it
but I had to do it.

1177
01:09:18,744 --> 01:09:23,082
I said: "I know you're
surprised that we found you,

1178
01:09:23,115 --> 01:09:26,686
because we know
you as Rai Ghazarian.

1179
01:09:28,020 --> 01:09:30,823
But now that I know
you're Razmik Minasian,

1180
01:09:32,091 --> 01:09:34,127
what would you do

1181
01:09:34,159 --> 01:09:37,997
if someone was going to
hurt your son or daughter?

1182
01:09:38,030 --> 01:09:39,332
Think about it."

1183
01:09:48,007 --> 01:09:50,110
He signed
an affidavit stating

1184
01:09:50,142 --> 01:09:52,244
that I was
absolutely unknowing.

1185
01:09:53,178 --> 01:09:56,382
So I go to court January third
and the lady says to me:

1186
01:09:56,415 --> 01:09:58,351
"Erik, this is
what's going to happen:

1187
01:09:58,383 --> 01:10:00,753
The judge is going to give you
a two year prison sentence,

1188
01:10:00,787 --> 01:10:03,423
we're going to pay him 1,000
