1429
01:22:26,964 --> 01:22:29,502
And we ate all the food,
we shot the shit,

1430
01:22:29,534 --> 01:22:30,836
we played poker,
we played chess,

1431
01:22:30,869 --> 01:22:32,772
we talked about life.

1432
01:22:32,805 --> 01:22:35,007
I hung out that day,
I hung out a long time that day.

1433
01:22:35,039 --> 01:22:37,042
I hung out forever.

1434
01:22:37,074 --> 01:22:42,046
When I got called back
to my cell later on that day

1435
01:22:42,079 --> 01:22:44,751
I told Mourad:
"Hey, I'll see you next week."

1436
01:22:45,751 --> 01:22:47,019
He says <i>Inshallah.</i>

1437
01:22:47,052 --> 01:22:49,622
<i>Inshallah</i> means "God willing".

1438
01:22:49,654 --> 01:22:53,124
It's a normal saying
in Pakistan or in Urdu.

1439
01:22:53,158 --> 01:22:55,428
It's "Hey, you'll get out of
here soon, <i>Inshallah."</i>

1440
01:22:55,461 --> 01:22:59,731
Or "Hopefully the judge will go
easy on you soon, <i>Inshallah."</i>

1441
01:23:01,065 --> 01:23:03,135
"I'll see you
next week, <i>Inshallah."</i>

1442
01:23:04,101 --> 01:23:08,507
And the next morning
he was hung.

1443
01:23:12,744 --> 01:23:13,746
He'd...

1444
01:23:18,950 --> 01:23:21,020
shared his last meal
with me.

1445
01:23:21,052 --> 01:23:23,756
He had it prepared so that
I'd enjoy it not him.

1446
01:23:25,022 --> 01:23:26,057
And...

1447
01:23:29,761 --> 01:23:30,897
And he didn't tell me.

1448
01:23:43,775 --> 01:23:47,812
One day, Joey Paul
Jensen knocks on my office

1449
01:23:47,846 --> 01:23:50,583
and she said:
"You know Sherry

1450
01:23:50,615 --> 01:23:52,851
I have this gentlemen

1451
01:23:52,885 --> 01:23:55,820
his name is Scott,
I forget his last name,

1452
01:23:55,854 --> 01:23:58,223
but I have this gentleman

1453
01:23:58,257 --> 01:24:00,125
who went to school with

1454
01:24:00,158 --> 01:24:03,995
the son of the
president of Pakistan,

1455
01:24:04,029 --> 01:24:06,031
Pervez Musharraf's son."

1456
01:24:13,171 --> 01:24:16,008
Mr. Musharraf says to me:

1457
01:24:16,040 --> 01:24:18,711
"So what is it
you would like me to do?"

1458
01:24:20,044 --> 01:24:24,249
And I said:
"I have here a letter

1459
01:24:24,283 --> 01:24:27,919
that I would ask that
you present to your brother."

1460
01:24:27,953 --> 01:24:30,189
You know,
president Pervez Musharraf.

1461
01:24:32,257 --> 01:24:34,827
"Ask him for
clemency for my son."

1462
01:24:36,093 --> 01:24:39,531
She was using
every resource she had

1463
01:24:39,565 --> 01:24:41,734
just personally,
socially, and financially

1464
01:24:41,766 --> 01:24:44,936
and that wasn't
an endless pipeline.

1465
01:24:44,970 --> 01:24:49,141
And so it was fortuitous
that I knew this person

1466
01:24:49,173 --> 01:24:51,310
that somehow was connected

1467
01:24:51,342 --> 01:24:54,846
in ways that I
couldn't even describe.

1468
01:24:54,879 --> 01:24:58,217
