the Taliban

1495
01:26:24,069 --> 01:26:28,106
that resulted in
a short-term ceasefire

1496
01:26:28,140 --> 01:26:30,409
and some advancements.

1497
01:26:30,441 --> 01:26:33,412
And so I knew enough
of the leaders there

1498
01:26:33,445 --> 01:26:36,248
that I got involved.

1499
01:26:36,280 --> 01:26:38,783
I get a visit from my lawyer
and I tell him okay

1500
01:26:38,816 --> 01:26:40,819
we're going to go to the courts

1501
01:26:40,851 --> 01:26:43,822
and we're going
to see what we can do.

1502
01:26:45,089 --> 01:26:47,994
As we were coming out
of two-cell and up the path

1503
01:26:48,959 --> 01:26:50,729
one of the deputy
superintendents

1504
01:26:50,762 --> 01:26:52,731
and all his numberdards
started praying for me.

1505
01:26:52,763 --> 01:26:54,999
And literally as I was walking
up to the front of the prison

1506
01:26:55,033 --> 01:26:58,102
all the guards
and different prisoners

1507
01:26:58,136 --> 01:27:01,040
were in unison just giving
me a nice little blessing.

1508
01:27:01,073 --> 01:27:04,843
And I thought to myself
wow this changed.

1509
01:27:04,876 --> 01:27:08,079
When I came in here,
I came in swinging.

1510
01:27:08,113 --> 01:27:12,685
And here I was with
potentially good news

1511
01:27:12,717 --> 01:27:14,452
about to be given to me.
I might be leaving soon.

1512
01:27:14,485 --> 01:27:16,387
And here's everyone
whose attitudes

1513
01:27:16,421 --> 01:27:18,323
have all changed
towards me.

1514
01:27:18,355 --> 01:27:20,291
It felt... It felt good.

1515
01:27:21,258 --> 01:27:24,163
I appreciated that.

1516
01:27:24,195 --> 01:27:27,098
But also I didn't want to
get my hopes up.

1517
01:27:27,132 --> 01:27:31,136
I kept telling myself:
"Erik if it's bad news

1518
01:27:31,168 --> 01:27:33,171
and you to end up
being here for seven years

1519
01:27:33,204 --> 01:27:35,339
you can do it.
Everything's going to be fine.

1520
01:27:35,373 --> 01:27:37,910
You've made a good life
for yourself here."

1521
01:27:38,944 --> 01:27:41,847
I always reminded myself
it could always be worse.

1522
01:27:43,381 --> 01:27:44,950
I just didn't want to
get my hopes up.

1523
01:27:44,982 --> 01:27:47,953
And as I went
into the front office

1524
01:27:47,985 --> 01:27:49,454
and down the hallway

1525
01:27:49,488 --> 01:27:51,390
I started questioning
myself, what if, though?

1526
01:27:51,422 --> 01:27:55,393
What if? What if?
And I go around the corner

1527
01:27:55,427 --> 01:27:57,396
towards
the Superintendent's office

1528
01:27:57,428 --> 01:27:59,198
and it was the prison doctor
that came around the corner

1529
01:27:59,230 --> 01:28:01,966
